HEADWORD: Malayan tapir
<hw>Malayan tapir</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A large
inoffensive chiefly nocturnal ungulate (<spn>Tapirus indicus</spn>) of
tropical America and Southeast Asia having a heavy body and fleshy
snout.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Indian tapir, <spn>Tapirus indicus</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Malay Archipelago</ent>⟦br⟧
